1. Create a vpc with 4 subnets two public and two private
   a. use vpc and more ( name the vpc abc )

2. ec2 
   a. create a sg called abc-ec2-sg
   b. allow http and ssh from every where and allow all outbound traffic
   c. create two ec2 in abc vpc, one in us-east-1a public subnet
                      one in us-east-1b public subnet
   d. use this user data
      #!/bin/bash
      dnf install httpd php php-mysqlnd -y 
      systemctl start httpd
      echo hello $(hostname) > /var/www/html/index.html
   e. access the public ip of your instances and make sure that they are working fine

3. target group
  a. create a target group called abc-tg
  b. port 80 
  c. use abc vpc 
  d. add the EC2s created instances to the target group

4. loadbalancer
  a. create a security group called alb-sg, allow http from every where and allow all outbound traffic
  
